      <comment>/* CGPM meetings */[[WP:CHECKWIKI]] error 61 fixes + [[WP:GENFIXES|general fixes]], References after punctuation per [[WP:REFPUNC]] and [[WP:PAIC]] using [[Project:AWB|AWB]] (7671)</comment>
      <text xml:space="preserve">The '''General Conference on Weights and Measures''' is the English name of the '''Conférence générale des poids et mesures''' ('''CGPM''', never GCWM). It is one of the three organizations established to maintain the [[International System of Units]] (SI) under the terms of the ''Convention du Mètre'' ([[Metre Convention]]) of 1875. It meets in [[Sèvres]] (in the southwestern suburbs of Paris) every four to six years. The CGPM represents 52 member states and 26 further associate members.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.bipm.org/en/convention/member_states/ CGPM Member States]&lt;/ref&gt;

== CGPM meetings ==
{| width=&quot;100%&quot;
|width=&quot;11%&quot; valign=&quot;top&quot;|[http://www.bipm.org/jsp/en/ListCGPMResolution.jsp?CGPM=1 1st] (1889)
|width=&quot;90%&quot; |kilogram defined as mass of the international prototype kilogram (IPK) made of [[platinum]]-[[iridium]] and kept at the [[International Bureau of Weights and Measures]] (Bureau international des poids et mesures), [[Sèvres]], France. International prototype metre sanctioned.
|-
| valign=&quot;top&quot;|[http://www.bipm.org/jsp/en/ListCGPMResolution.jsp?CGPM=2 2nd] (1897)
|No resolutions were passed by the 2nd CGPM.
|-
| valign=&quot;top&quot;|[http://www.bipm.org/jsp/en/ListCGPMResolution.jsp?CGPM=3 3rd] (1901)
|[[litre]] redefined as volume of 1&amp;nbsp;kg of water.  Clarified that kilograms are units of mass, &quot;standard weight&quot; defined, [[standard gravity|standard acceleration of gravity]] defined endorsing use of grams force and making them well-defined.
|-
| valign=&quot;top&quot;|[http://www.bipm.org/jsp/en/ListCGPMResolution.jsp?CGPM=4 4th] (1907)
|[[Carat (unit)|carat]] = 200&amp;nbsp;mg adopted.
|-
