|International Temperature Scale proposed.
|-
| valign=&quot;top&quot;|[http://www.bipm.org/jsp/en/ListCGPMResolution.jsp?CGPM=6 6th] (1921)
|Metre Convention revised.
|-
| valign=&quot;top&quot;|[http://www.bipm.org/jsp/en/ListCGPMResolution.jsp?CGPM=7 7th] (1927)
|Consultative Committee for Electricity (CCE) created.
|-
| valign=&quot;top&quot;|[http://www.bipm.org/jsp/en/ListCGPMResolution.jsp?CGPM=8 8th] (1933)
|Need for absolute electrical unit identified.
|-
| valign=&quot;top&quot;|[http://www.bipm.org/jsp/en/ListCGPMResolution.jsp?CGPM=9 9th] (1948)
|[[ampere]], [[bar (unit)|bar]], [[coulomb]], [[farad]], [[henry (unit)|henry]], [[joule]], [[newton (unit)|newton]], [[Ohm (unit)|ohm]], [[volt]], [[watt]], [[weber (unit)|weber]] defined. Chose [[Celsius|degree Celsius]] from among the three names then in use.  l (lowercase L) &lt;!--symbols for units of measure never italic--&gt;adopted as symbol for litre. Both the comma and dot on a line are accepted as decimal marker symbols. Symbols for the [[stere]] and second changed [http://www.bipm.org/jsp/en/ViewCGPMResolution.jsp?CGPM=9&amp;RES=7]. The universal return to the [[Long and short scales|Long Scale]] numbering system was proposed but not adopted.
|-
| valign=&quot;top&quot;|[http://www.bipm.org/jsp/en/ListCGPMResolution.jsp?CGPM=10 10th] (1954)
|[[kelvin]], [[standard atmosphere]] defined. ''International System of Units'' (metre, kilogram, second, [[ampere]], [[kelvin]], [[candela]]) began.
|-
| valign=&quot;top&quot;|[http://www.bipm.org/jsp/en/ListCGPMResolution.jsp?CGPM=11 11th] (1960)
|metre redefined in terms of wavelengths of light. Units: [[hertz]], [[lumen (unit)|lumen]], [[lux]], [[tesla (unit)|tesla]] adopted. New metric system given the official symbol '''SI''' for '''''[[Système International d'Unités]]''''', the &quot;modernized metric system&quot;. Prefixes ''[[pico-]]'', ''[[nano-]]'', ''[[micro-]]'', ''[[mega-]]'', ''[[giga-]]'' and ''[[tera-]]'' confirmed.
|-
| valign=&quot;top&quot;|[http://www.bipm.org/jsp/en/ListCGPMResolution.jsp?CGPM=12 12th] (1964)
|original definition of [[litre]] = 1 dm&lt;sup&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt; restored. ''[[atto-]]'' and ''[[femto-]]'' prefixes.
|-
| valign=&quot;top&quot;|[http://www.bipm.org/jsp/en/ListCGPMResolution.jsp?CGPM=13 13th] (1967)
|second redefined as duration of 9&amp;nbsp;192&amp;nbsp;631&amp;nbsp;770 periods of the radiation corresponding to the transition between the two hyperfine levels of the ground state of the [[caesium]]-133 atom at a temperature of 0 K. ''Degree Kelvin'' renamed ''kelvin''. Candela redefined.
|-
| valign=&quot;top&quot;|[http://www.bipm.org/jsp/en/ListCGPMResolution.jsp?CGPM=14 14th] (1971)
|new [[SI base unit]] [[mole (unit)|mole]] defined. [[Pascal (unit)|pascal]], [[siemens (unit)|siemens]] approved.
|-
| valign=&quot;top&quot;|[http://www.bipm.org/jsp/en/ListCGPMResolution.jsp?CGPM=15 15th] (1975)
|''[[peta-]]'' and ''[[exa-]]'' prefixes. [[gray (unit)|gray]] and [[becquerel]] radiological units.
|-
| valign=&quot;top&quot;|[http://www.bipm.org/jsp/en/ListCGPMResolution.jsp?CGPM=16 16th] (1979)
|[[candela]], [[sievert]] defined. Both l and L &lt;!--symbols for units of measure never italic--&gt; provisionally allowed as symbols for litre.
|-
| valign=&quot;top&quot;|[http://www.bipm.org/jsp/en/ListCGPMResolution.jsp?CGPM=17 17th] (1983)
|metre redefined in terms of the speed of light, but keeps same length.
|-
| valign=&quot;top&quot;|[http://www.bipm.org/jsp/en/ListCGPMResolution.jsp?CGPM=18 18th] (1987)
|conventional values adopted for [[Josephson constant]], ''K&lt;sub&gt;J&lt;/sub&gt;'', and [[von Klitzing constant]], ''R&lt;sub&gt;K&lt;/sub&gt;'', preparing the way for alternative definitions of the ampere and kilogram.
|-
| valign=&quot;top&quot;|[http://www.bipm.org/jsp/en/ListCGPMResolution.jsp?CGPM=19 19th] (1991)
|new prefixes ''[[yocto-]]'', ''[[zepto-]]'', ''[[zetta-]]'' and ''[[yotta-]]''.
|-
| valign=&quot;top&quot;|[http://www.bipm.org/jsp/en/ListCGPMResolution.jsp?CGPM=20 20th] (1995)
|[[SI supplementary unit]]s ([[radian]] and [[steradian]]) become ''derived units''.
|-
| valign=&quot;top&quot;|[http://www.bipm.org/jsp/en/ListCGPMResolution.jsp?CGPM=21 21st] (1999)
|new SI derived unit, the [[katal]] = [[mole (unit)|mole]] per second, for the expression of catalytic activity.
|-
| valign=&quot;top&quot;|[http://www.bipm.org/jsp/en/ListCGPMResolution.jsp?CGPM=22 22nd] (2003)
|A comma or a dot on a line are reaffirmed as decimal marker symbols, and not as grouping symbols in order to facilitate reading; &quot;numbers may be divided in groups of three in order to facilitate reading; neither dots nor commas are ever inserted in the spaces between groups&quot;.&lt;ref&gt;http://www.bipm.org/jsp/en/ViewCGPMResolution.jsp?CGPM=22&amp;RES=10&lt;/ref&gt;
|-
| valign=&quot;top&quot;|[http://www.bipm.org/jsp/en/ListCGPMResolution.jsp?CGPM=23 23rd] (2007)
|clarification about the kelvin and thoughts about possible revision of certain base units
|}

