|-
! [[Magnetic field|magnetic B field]] 
| style=&quot;text-align:center;&quot;|'''B'''|| 1 [[tesla (unit)|T]] || = (10&lt;sup&gt;4&lt;/sup&gt; ''c''&lt;sup&gt;−1&lt;/sup&gt;) statT || = (10&lt;sup&gt;4&lt;/sup&gt;) [[Gauss (unit)|G]] || = (10&lt;sup&gt;4&lt;/sup&gt;) [[Gauss (unit)|G]] 
|-
! [[Magnetic field|magnetic H field]] 
| style=&quot;text-align:center;&quot;|'''H'''|| 1 [[Ampere|A]]/[[Metre|m]] || = (4π 10&lt;sup&gt;−3&lt;/sup&gt; ''c'') statA/[[Centimetre|cm]] || = (4π 10&lt;sup&gt;−3&lt;/sup&gt;) [[oersted|Oe]] || = (4π 10&lt;sup&gt;−3&lt;/sup&gt;) [[oersted|Oe]]
|-
! [[magnetic dipole moment]] 
| style=&quot;text-align:center;&quot;|'''μ'''|| 1 [[Ampere|A]]·[[Square metre|m²]] || = (10&lt;sup&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt; ''c'') statA·cm² || = (10&lt;sup&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt;) [[Abampere|abA]]·cm² || = (10&lt;sup&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt;) [[erg]]/[[Gauss (unit)|G]] 
|-
! [[magnetic flux]]
| style=&quot;text-align:center;&quot;|''Φ&lt;sub&gt;m&lt;/sub&gt;''|| 1 [[Weber (unit)|Wb]]|| = (10&lt;sup&gt;8&lt;/sup&gt; ''c''&lt;sup&gt;−1&lt;/sup&gt;) statT·cm² || = (10&lt;sup&gt;8&lt;/sup&gt;) [[Maxwell (unit)|Mw]] || = (10&lt;sup&gt;8&lt;/sup&gt;) [[Gauss (unit)|G]]·cm² 
|-
! [[electrical resistance|resistance]]
| style=&quot;text-align:center;&quot;|''R''|| 1 [[Ohm|Ω]] || = (10&lt;sup&gt;9&lt;/sup&gt; ''c''&lt;sup&gt;-2&lt;/sup&gt;) [[Second|s]]/[[Centimetre|cm]]|| = (10&lt;sup&gt;9&lt;/sup&gt;)  [[Abohm|abΩ]] || = (10&lt;sup&gt;9&lt;/sup&gt; ''c''&lt;sup&gt;−2&lt;/sup&gt;) [[Second|s]]/[[Centimetre|cm]]
|-
! [[electrical resistivity|resistivity]]
| style=&quot;text-align:center;&quot;|''ρ'' || 1 [[Ohm|Ω]]·[[Metre|m]] || = (10&lt;sup&gt;11&lt;/sup&gt; ''c''&lt;sup&gt;-2&lt;/sup&gt;) [[Second|s]] || = (10&lt;sup&gt;11&lt;/sup&gt;)  [[Abohm|abΩ]]·[[Centimetre|cm]] || = (10&lt;sup&gt;11&lt;/sup&gt; ''c''&lt;sup&gt;−2&lt;/sup&gt;) [[Second|s]]
|-
! [[capacitance]]
| style=&quot;text-align:center;&quot;|''C''|| 1 [[Farad|F]] || = (10&lt;sup&gt;-9&lt;/sup&gt; ''c''&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;) [[Centimetre|cm]]|| = (10&lt;sup&gt;-9&lt;/sup&gt;)  [[Abfarad|abF]] || = (10&lt;sup&gt;-9&lt;/sup&gt; ''c''&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;) [[Centimetre|cm]]
|-
! [[inductance]]
| style=&quot;text-align:center;&quot;|''L''|| 1 [[Henry (unit)|H]] || = (10&lt;sup&gt;9&lt;/sup&gt; ''c''&lt;sup&gt;-2&lt;/sup&gt;) [[Centimetre|cm]]&lt;sup&gt;-1&lt;/sup&gt;·[[Second|s]]&lt;sup&gt;-2&lt;/sup&gt;|| = (10&lt;sup&gt;9&lt;/sup&gt;)  [[Abhenry|abH]] || = (10&lt;sup&gt;9&lt;/sup&gt; ''c''&lt;sup&gt;−2&lt;/sup&gt;) [[Centimetre|cm]]&lt;sup&gt;−1&lt;/sup&gt;·[[Second|s]]&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; 
|}

In this table, ''c'' = 29,979,245,800 ≈ 3·10&lt;sup&gt;10&lt;/sub&gt; is the [[speed of light]] in vacuum in the CGS units of cm/s.

One can think of the SI value of the [[Coulomb constant]] ''k&lt;sub&gt;C&lt;/sub&gt;'' as:
:&lt;math&gt;k_C=\frac{1}{4\pi\epsilon_0}=\frac{\mu_0 (c/100)^2}{4\pi}=10^{-7}\cdot 10^{-4}\cdot c^2 = 10^{-11}\cdot c^2 .&lt;/math&gt;
This explains why SI to ESU conversions involving factors of ''c&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;'' lead to significant simplifications of the ESU units, such as 1 statF = 1&amp;nbsp;cm and 1 statΩ = 1 s/cm: this is the consequence of the fact that in ESU system ''k&lt;sub&gt;C&lt;/sub&gt;''=1. For example, a centimetre of capacitance is the capacitance between a sphere of radius 1&amp;nbsp;cm in vacuum and infinity. The capacitance ''C'' between two concentric spheres of radii ''R'' and ''r'' in ESU CGS system is:
: &lt;math&gt;\frac{1}{\frac{1}{r}-\frac{1}{R}}&lt;/math&gt;.
By taking the limit as ''R'' goes to infinity we see ''C'' equals ''r''.

