'''CD''', '''C/D''', '''Cd''' or '''cd''' may stand for:
* [[Compact Disc]], a thin plastic silvery disc for audio recordings
** [[CD-ROM]], the same technology used for computer data
* [[Certificate of deposit]], bank account in the United States with a fixed maturity date
* CD (500 minus 100) represents [[400 (number)|400]] in [[Roman numerals]]
* CD can stand for &quot;Cross Dresser&quot; See [[transvestism]]

{{TOC right}}

==In science and computers==
* [[.cd]], the Internet domain of the Democratic Republic of the Congo
* [[Cadmium]] (chemical element Cd)
* [[Candela]] (cd, a unit of light intensity)
* [[Circular dichroism]], a form of spectroscopy
* [[Drag coefficient]] (C&lt;sub&gt;d&lt;/sub&gt;)
* [[Cluster of differentiation]] in cell surface markers
* [[Cordoba Durchmusterung]], a star catalogue of the southern sky; stars are listed in the catalog by numbers prefixed with &quot;CD&quot;
* cD galaxy, sometimes also known as [[brightest cluster galaxy]]
* [[Cyclodextrin]] (a family of cyclic oligosaccharides)
* In psychiatry, [[physical dependence]], or chemical dependency
* [[cd (command)]], a shell command to change directory

