|ends = 2 [[Tevet]] or 3 [[Tevet]]
|celebrations = Lighting [[candle]]s each night. Singing special songs, such as [[Ma'oz Tzur]]. Reciting [[Hallel]] prayer. Eating foods fried in oil, such as [[latke]]s and [[sufganiyot]], and dairy foods. Playing the ''[[Hanukkah#Dreidel|dreidel]]'' game, and giving [[Hanukkah#Hanukkah gelt|Hanukkah ''gelt'']]
|type = Jewish festival
|significance = The [[Maccabees]] successfully rebelled against [[Antiochus IV Epiphanes]]. The Temple was purified and the wicks of the menorah miraculously burned for eight days, even though there was only enough sacred oil for one day's lighting.
|relatedto = [[Purim]], as a [[rabbi]]nically decreed holiday.
|date2011 = Sunset, December 20 to sunset, December 28
|date2012 = Sunset, December 8 to sunset, December 16
